{"source_key":"sha256-03e2bb4f67dc5906b23b3975517ad614","record_index":286,"record_hash":"sha256:6475e3c7427a852baed37088289bd28de7f42bc786cb71417b1dfef7ba0433e7","timestamp":"2026-05-21T19:42:06.087Z","kind":"message","source_event_kind":"claude:assistant:text","role":"assistant","text":"I ran the full maintainability playbook on the `agentlog-turn-storage` branch's changes to `crates/but-agentlog` (the two commits, ~22 files). Baseline was green before I started; I read the whole crate, ran 7 focused review subagents (deletion, boundary, execution-trace, Rust, test, security/privacy, performance), triaged, and made small behavior-preserving edits.\n\n## What I changed\n\n| # | Change | File(s) | Why |\n|---|--------|---------|-----|\n| A | Deleted dead `RelatedTarget::matched_by()` + its unused `_matched_by` param/arg | `gitmeta/read.rs`, `gitmeta/session_outline.rs` | Fully dead code chain |\n| B | `redact_named_secret_values` now patches `lower` in place instead of rebuilding `to_ascii_lowercase()` of the whole string on every match | `redaction.rs` | Removes O(N²) on long values; runs per stored record |\n| C | Hoisted duplicated `push_unique` into `outline_support` | `outline_support.rs`, `session_outline.rs`, `timeline_outline.rs` | Verbatim copy in two modules |\n| D | Replaced `record_agent_log`'s 4-tuple return with named `RecordedAgentLog` struct | `cli.rs` | Both call sites discarded different pairs with `_, _` |\n| E | Added 3 redaction tests: domain-sensitive-key contract (`branch`/`cwd`/`path`), embedded-UUID, short-secret known-limit | `redaction.rs` | Pins the security-critical contract; no behavior change |\n\n**Behavior:** unchanged. B produces byte-identical output (REDACTION is ASCII, so `lower` stays aligned). I respected your constraint — the deliberately-public, currently-uncalled forward-looking API in `lib.rs` (`list_sessions`, `find_related_sessions`, `get_session_timeline`, `get_related_session_detail`, etc.) was treated as intentional and left intact.\n\n**Validation (all green):** `cargo fmt --check`, `cargo test -p but-agentlog` (**61 pass**, +3 new), `cargo check -p but --features agentlog`, `cargo clippy -p but-agentlog --all-targets`, `cargo machete`.\n\n## Deliberately NOT changed — worth your decision\n\nTwo are design calls I didn't want to make unilaterally, and they pull in opposite directions — together they're really one **\"tune the redaction policy\"** decision:\n\n1. **Environment block stored un-redacted** (security P1): `TurnDetail.environment` (worktree file paths) and branch *display names* are serialized straight to GitMeta and **synced to the remote** without `redact_text`. Note: the `observed_targets` *keys* (e.g. `ref:refs/heads/main`) **must** stay verbatim — they're the lookup index, so they can't be blindly redacted. Worktree paths/branch names are the part you could redact.\n2. **Over-redaction of `path`/`id`/`branch` keys** (security P2): `is_sensitive_key` fully redacts any `path`/`cwd`/`file_path`/`*_id` key, so Read/Edit tool-input paths collapse to `[REDACTED]`, gutting transcript diagnostic value.\n\nOther documented-only items (real, but too invasive for a cleanup pass on a POC): read-side matches `RecordKind` via magic strings instead of deserializing the enum; ~5× repo discovery/`Session::open` per capture; `skim` reads each session's turn-details + full transcript ~2× and re-parses turn summaries 3×; `cap_tool_result_text` truncates before redaction (a secret on the seam could split); keyless short secrets are inherently undetectable (consider known-prefix patterns like `ghp_`/`sk-`/`AKIA`).\n\nWant me to act on either redaction-policy item, or open follow-ups for the documented-only findings?","tool_name":null,"tool_input":null,"source_record":{"parentUuid":"[REDACTED:entropy]","isSidechain":false,"message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-7","id":"[REDACTED:entropy]","type":"message","role":"assistant","diagnostics":null,"stop_reason":"end_turn","stop_sequence":null,"s